cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques for monocular depth estimation. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for depth estimation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of semantic information for training CNNs, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of depth estimation for autonomous driving and driver assistance, which falls under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics).
